==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|valva|lang=la}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A device that controls the flow of a gas or fluid through a pipe.
# A device that admits fuel and air into the cylinder of an internal combustion engine, or one that allows combustion gases to exit.
# {{anatomy}} A structure (for example in the heart) that controls the direction of the flow of the blood.
# {{UK}} A [[vacuum tube]].
# {{biology}} One of the paired, hinged shells of some mollusks and of brachiopods.
# {{biology}} One of the two silicified halves of the cell wall of a diatom.
# {{biology}} The entire, single-piece shell of a snail and some other mollusks.
# {{botany}} One of the sections into which a dehiscent fruit breaks

